<section class="py-20 px-6 bg-slate-50">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-[#0C447C] mb-6">Every AI coding session starts cold.</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
      <p>You open Claude Code, Cursor, or Windsurf. The AI has no idea what you decided yesterday. No memory of the patterns you established. No clue about the approach you tried and rejected.</p>
      <p>So you spend the first 20 minutes re-explaining your project. Again.</p>
      <p class="font-medium text-[#0C447C]">Lodestar fixes this. One command at the end of each session. One command at the start of the next. Your AI picks up exactly where you left off.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
